main event: A civilian discovered a material identified as radar chaff in the back of his house in Williamston, Michigan in May 1967.
interesting points: The observer found the material while mowing his lawn,The observer had previously seen a spaceship in the area,The material was reported to the Air Force for analysis,It was confirmed that the material was dropped by military aircraft to confuse radar operators,The analysis indicated that there was likely a radar exercise in the vicinity around that time.
sighted object: unknown object associated with radar chaff
witness description: civilian, concerned about the material due to previous UFO sightings in the area
